article.headline: Tulane 50, Southern Miss 47
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Tulane held Southern Miss without a field goal for the final 8:22 to hold on for a 50-47 win Wednesday night. Andrew Garcia sparked a Green Wave (11-15, 6-7 Conference USA) comeback with four second-half steals, buried the go-ahead 3-pointer with 4:34 to go and added the game-clinching free throws with 15.9 seconds remaining. Tulane was behind 43-35 with 8:22 to go after Southern Miss (8-20, 2-11) buried four straight 3-pointers. But Tulane harassed Southern Miss into missing their final eight shots while turning the ball over five times in that same stretch. With 1:11 to go, Southern Miss cracked the scoring column again with a pair of free throws from Kyle Lamonte, who had a career-high 19 points off the bench. Two more Lamonte foul shots with 20.3 seconds on the clock made it a one-point game, but Garcia's free throws provided the final margin. Quincy Davis led Tulane with 20 points. Chris Moore added 11 and David Gomez had 10. Lamonte led Southern Miss with 19 points and Craig Craft had 11.
